HEADWORD: Rostrated
<hw>Ros"tra*ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>rostratus</ets>, fr.
<ets>rostrum</ets> a beak. See <er>Rostrum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having a process resembling the beak of a bird; beaked;
